{"source_key":"sha256-5554f84e350d12a12ce22886a954582c","record_index":1452,"record_hash":"sha256:cad7c2b805af605e79d63b056c49e02a0908528f05385de4b2be03d3241b3cf0","timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:41:29.263Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Change-now: none. This pass is coherent.\\n\\n`AssociationReason` removal is the right call: the query target already tells you whether the evidence is branch/review/change, and the spec wants `turn_keys`, score, confidence, and scoring version, not a parallel reason enum. See [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:163) and [Including-turns.md](/Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02%[REDACTED:entropy].md:621).\\n\\nThe new detail API is minimal enough. `RelatedTurnWindow`, `RelatedTimelineTurn`, and `RelatedSessionDetail` are only exposed because `get_related_session_detail` needs them at the public boundary, and [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:12) re-exports exactly that surface. The implementation stays index-first, verifies candidates, then hydrates only the requested turn window: [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:388).\\n\\nLater: tighten the spec wording around `getSessionTimeline(session_key, window?)`. The Rust API is currently just “latest N turns” via `max_turns`: [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:365). That’s fine for now, but the doc’s `window?` wording at [Including-turns.md](/Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02%[REDACTED:entropy].md:749) could imply a richer cursor/range shape.\\n\\nValidation: `cargo test -p but-agentlog --lib` passes, 39/39.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:41:29.263Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}